<br>
We've been paying 10 bucks a month, we've payed (most of us full priced as well) for 3 expansions. This is not mention the time we've invested which I admit in a business sense they owe us nothing for, but in an ethical sense, in an customer service sense it sends a startling message. This is a kick in the tenders plain and simple, and to be honest I'm really surprised they've done it, the outcry against it, the fact that they've been listening to the player base a lot more since viable alternatives have started appearing. But now it's back to milk the addicts for money again...<br>
<br>
and actually taliewin, many many people have been bitching at that which does not exist, one of the reasons why they decided to shut down the official forums, (though yes the flames were getting out of hand the gestapo approach was not the right way)<br>
